80#define GLEW_STATIC
81
82//#pragma warning( disable : 4273)
83#ifndef __glew_h__
84#define __glew_h__
85#define __GLEW_H__
86
87#if defined(__gl_h_) || defined(__GL_H__) || defined(_GL_H) || defined(__X_GL_H)
88#error gl.h included before glew.h
89#endif
90#if defined(__gl2_h_)
91#error gl2.h included before glew.h
92#endif
93#if defined(__gltypes_h_)
94#error gltypes.h included before glew.h
95#endif
96#if defined(__REGAL_H__)
97#error Regal.h included before glew.h
98#endif
99#if defined(__glext_h_) || defined(__GLEXT_H_)
100#error glext.h included before glew.h
101#endif
102#if defined(__gl_ATI_h_)
103#error glATI.h included before glew.h
104#endif
105
106#define __gl_h_
107#define __gl2_h_
108#define __GL_H__
109#define _GL_H
110#define __gltypes_h_
111#define __REGAL_H__
112#define __X_GL_H
113#define __glext_h_
114#define __GLEXT_H_
115#define __gl_ATI_h_
116
117#if defined(_WIN32)
118
119/*
120 * GLEW does not include <windows.h> to avoid name space pollution.
121 * GL needs GLAPI and GLAPIENTRY, GLU needs APIENTRY, CALLBACK, and wchar_t
122 * defined properly.
123 */
124/* <windef.h> and <gl.h>*/
125#ifdef APIENTRY
126# ifndef GLAPIENTRY
127# define GLAPIENTRY APIENTRY
128# endif
129# ifndef GLEWAPIENTRY
130# define GLEWAPIENTRY APIENTRY
131# endif
132#else
133#define GLEW_APIENTRY_DEFINED
134# if defined(__MINGW32__) || defined(__CYGWIN__) || (_MSC_VER >= 800) || defined(_STDCALL_SUPPORTED) || defined(__BORLANDC__)
135# define APIENTRY __stdcall
136# ifndef GLAPIENTRY
137# define GLAPIENTRY __stdcall
138# endif
139# ifndef GLEWAPIENTRY
140# define GLEWAPIENTRY __stdcall
141# endif
142# else
143# define APIENTRY
144# endif
145#endif
146#ifndef GLAPI
147# if defined(__MINGW32__) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
148# define GLAPI extern
149# endif
150#endif
151/* <winnt.h> */
152#ifndef CALLBACK
153#define GLEW_CALLBACK_DEFINED
154# if defined(__MINGW32__) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
155# define CALLBACK __attribute__ ((__stdcall__))
156# elif (defined(_M_MRX000) || defined(_M_IX86) || defined(_M_ALPHA) || defined(_M_PPC)) && !defined(MIDL_PASS)
157# define CALLBACK __stdcall
158# else
159# define CALLBACK
160# endif
161#endif
162/* <wingdi.h> and <winnt.h> */
163#ifndef WINGDIAPI
164#define GLEW_WINGDIAPI_DEFINED
165#define WINGDIAPI __declspec(dllimport)
166#endif
167/* <ctype.h> */
168#if (defined(_MSC_VER) || defined(__BORLANDC__)) && !defined(_WCHAR_T_DEFINED)
169typedef unsigned short wchar_t;
170# define _WCHAR_T_DEFINED
171#endif
172/* <stddef.h> */
173#if !defined(_W64)
174# if !defined(__midl) && (defined(_X86_) || defined(_M_IX86)) && defined(_MSC_VER) && _MSC_VER >= 1300
175# define _W64 __w64
176# else
177# define _W64
178# endif
179#endif
180#if !defined(_PTRDIFF_T_DEFINED) && !defined(_PTRDIFF_T_) && !defined(__MINGW64__)
181# ifdef _WIN64
182typedef __int64 ptrdiff_t;
183# else
184typedef _W64 int ptrdiff_t;
185# endif
186# define _PTRDIFF_T_DEFINED
187# define _PTRDIFF_T_
188#endif
189
190#ifndef GLAPI
191# if defined(__MINGW32__) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
192# define GLAPI extern
193# else
194# define GLAPI WINGDIAPI
195# endif
196#endif
197
198/*
199 * GLEW_STATIC is defined for static library.
200 * GLEW_BUILD is defined for building the DLL library.
201 */
202
203#ifdef GLEW_STATIC
204# define GLEWAPI extern
205#else
206# ifdef GLEW_BUILD
207# define GLEWAPI extern __declspec(dllexport)
208# else
209# define GLEWAPI extern __declspec(dllimport)
210# endif
211#endif
212
213#else /* _UNIX */
214
215/*
216 * Needed for ptrdiff_t in turn needed by VBO. This is defined by ISO
217 * C. On my system, this amounts to _3 lines_ of included code, all of
218 * them pretty much harmless. If you know of a way of detecting 32 vs
219 * 64 _targets_ at compile time you are free to replace this with
220 * something that's portable. For now, _this_ is the portable solution.
221 * (mem, 2004-01-04)
222 */
223
224#include <stddef.h>
225
226/* SGI MIPSPro doesn't like stdint.h in C++ mode */
227/* ID: 3376260 Solaris 9 has inttypes.h, but not stdint.h */
228
229#if (defined(__sgi) || defined(__sun)) && !defined(__GNUC__)
230#include <inttypes.h>
231#else
232#include <stdint.h>
233#endif
234
235#define GLEW_APIENTRY_DEFINED
236#define APIENTRY
237
238/*
239 * GLEW_STATIC is defined for static library.
240 */
241
242#ifdef GLEW_STATIC
243# define GLEWAPI extern
244#else
245# if defined(__GNUC__) && __GNUC__>=4
246# define GLEWAPI extern __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
247# elif defined(__SUNPRO_C) || defined(__SUNPRO_CC)
248# define GLEWAPI extern __global
249# else
250# define GLEWAPI extern
251# endif
252#endif
253
254/* <glu.h> */
255#ifndef GLAPI
256#define GLAPI extern
257#endif
258
259#endif /* _WIN32 */
260
261#ifndef GLAPIENTRY
262#define GLAPIENTRY
263#endif
264
265#ifndef GLEWAPIENTRY
266#define GLEWAPIENTRY
267#endif

288typedef unsigned long GLulong;

290typedef float GLclampf;
291typedef double GLdouble;
292typedef double GLclampd;
293typedef void GLvoid;
294#if defined(_MSC_VER) && _MSC_VER < 1400
295typedef __int64 GLint64EXT;
296typedef unsigned __int64 GLuint64EXT;
297#elif defined(_MSC_VER) || defined(__BORLANDC__)
298typedef signed long long GLint64EXT;
299typedef unsigned long long GLuint64EXT;
300#else
301# if defined(__MINGW32__) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
302#include <inttypes.h>
303# endif
304typedef int64_t GLint64EXT;
305typedef uint64_t GLuint64EXT;
306#endif
307typedef GLint64EXT GLint64;
308typedef GLuint64EXT GLuint64;
309typedef struct __GLsync *GLsync;
